### Why using github classroom
1. the git repositoy is good for a heterogeneous set of file formats including source code, binary code, graphics, PDF, and text files
2. excellent version control  & easier to get access to the students' files
3. instructors - can see the design of the students as they make progress
from http://rijndael.ece.vt.edu/schaum//blog/ghclassroom/ programming course



